{"id":14881018,"mediaExerciseId":"e29b91f8-d6d0-445f-86be-197f2b042cf1","exerciseName":"80","chapterName":"6","chapterTitle":"Discounted Cash Flow Valuation","groupId":612301,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":192,"solutions":[{"id":6372303,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will look at the Rule of 69.3 in estimating the time it takes for an investment to double. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The Rule of 69.3, just like the Rule of 72, is an estimation that allows us to predict how long it takes for an investment to double. It functions basically by dividing $69.3$ by the given rate.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Time}&=\\dfrac{69.3}{\\text{Rate}}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"In order to prove that the Rule of 69.3 is applicable to continuously compounded interest, we will first recall the formula. \n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Price at time t}&=\\text{Initial investment} \\times e^{\\text{rate} \\times \\text{time}}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nFor this, we will use an initial investment of $\\$1$ and rate of $10\\%$.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Substituting the values, we will get:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{Price}&=\\$1 \\times e^{0.10 \\times 6.93}\\\\[15 pt]\n&=\\$1.9997\\\\\n&\\approx \\$2\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nFrom this, we can show that the Rule of 69.3 is applicable to a continuously compounding interest. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"b9ab8d62-29a0-48d8-a8ae-d8f3e5e0c22d","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881020,"exerciseName":"1","page":194,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"ea9efbd5-7c6d-42ca-a07f-db1cf3326873","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-1-ea9efbd5-7c6d-42ca-a07f-db1cf3326873"},{"id":14881021,"exerciseName":"2","page":194,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"5136b784-ebee-4915-b92a-581efba3736e","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-2-5136b784-ebee-4915-b92a-581efba3736e"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881017,"exerciseName":"79","page":192,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"6312498a-e000-4114-9e6e-b6bc32c8b70e","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions-and-problems-79-6312498a-e000-4114-9e6e-b6bc32c8b70e"},{"id":14881016,"exerciseName":"78","page":192,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"35e767f6-c319-413c-b6bb-ec197607018c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-6-questions